1
00:01:33,493 --> 00:01:34,194
So

2
00:01:35,094 --> 00:01:36,362
I don't want you

3
00:01:37,130 --> 00:01:39,365
to feel the same regret I did.

4
00:01:41,868 --> 00:01:43,236
Please don't give up.

5
00:01:44,370 --> 00:01:45,472
I also don't want to see

6
00:01:46,039 --> 00:01:46,706
people like Sheng Nian

7
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:48,074
gain power

8
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:49,008
because of you.

9
00:01:49,576 --> 00:01:50,510
The ones who would suffer

10
00:01:50,710 --> 00:01:51,811
would be the patients, wouldn't they?

11
00:02:00,553 --> 00:02:01,721
Do you remember

12
00:02:02,789 --> 00:02:04,824
what you said on the rooftop that day?

13
00:02:05,492 --> 00:02:05,992
After all these years,

14
00:02:06,025 --> 00:02:07,026
you said I hadn't changed at all.

15
00:02:09,596 --> 00:02:10,430
But actually,

16
00:02:10,530 --> 00:02:12,398
the one who never changed was you.

17
00:02:13,333 --> 00:02:14,734
You've always been that pure

18
00:02:14,767 --> 00:02:15,635
idealist,

19
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:18,638
just the way I've always liked you.

20
00:02:19,405 --> 00:02:20,039
Director Zhou.

21
00:02:22,308 --> 00:02:23,042
Don't fold.

22
00:02:24,010 --> 00:02:25,478
You have to carry my ideals

23
00:02:26,312 --> 00:02:27,313
and keep going.

24
00:02:28,014 --> 00:02:28,481
Will you?

25
00:02:45,632 --> 00:02:46,065
Xiaofeng.

26
00:02:46,766 --> 00:02:47,433
I heard

27
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:49,169
Maiampere's business

28
00:02:49,569 --> 00:02:50,236
has been adjusted.

29
00:02:51,104 --> 00:02:51,504
Yes.

30
00:02:52,705 --> 00:02:53,406
Manager Ouyang

31
00:02:53,473 --> 00:02:54,841
is no longer responsible for Dongli.

32
00:02:55,241 --> 00:02:56,476
She has no connection with our hospital now.

33
00:02:57,610 --> 00:02:58,244
That's great.

34
00:03:00,213 --> 00:03:01,247
Like I've always said,

35
00:03:01,915 --> 00:03:04,884
you have wisdom

36
00:03:04,918 --> 00:03:05,552
beyond your years.

37
00:03:06,252 --> 00:03:07,120
You have a bright future.

38
00:03:08,521 --> 00:03:09,155
Thank you, President Wang.

39
00:03:10,023 --> 00:03:11,558
First, I'd like to thank the hospital leadership

40
00:03:11,591 --> 00:03:12,392
for trusting me

41
00:03:12,592 --> 00:03:14,093
with such a heavy responsibility.

42
00:03:15,395 --> 00:03:16,129
I also understand

43
00:03:16,195 --> 00:03:17,197
what you mentioned last time:

44
00:03:17,730 --> 00:03:18,865
performance is essential to the survival

45
00:03:19,065 --> 00:03:20,567
of the department and the hospital.

46
00:03:21,935 --> 00:03:23,436
But I believe you'll also agree

47
00:03:23,903 --> 00:03:24,704
that department building,

48
00:03:25,238 --> 00:03:26,039
discipline development,

49
00:03:26,806 --> 00:03:28,374
research, and talent cultivation

50
00:03:29,175 --> 00:03:30,610
must all be viewed long-term,

51
00:03:31,077 --> 00:03:32,245
not pursued for quick gains.

52
00:03:33,346 --> 00:03:34,480
So I'd like to discuss

53
00:03:34,847 --> 00:03:36,115
whether you could give me some time

54
00:03:36,683 --> 00:03:37,750
to use my own pace

55
00:03:37,784 --> 00:03:38,685
to develop the department.

56
00:03:48,795 --> 00:03:49,929
Of course I agree.

57
00:03:51,331 --> 00:03:51,998
Thank you, President.

58
00:03:52,365 --> 00:03:54,367
Since we've appointed you department director,

59
00:03:54,834 --> 00:03:57,070
it means we trust you.

60
00:03:58,371 --> 00:03:59,272
Like I've always said,

61
00:03:59,839 --> 00:04:00,807
if you encounter any difficulty,

62
00:04:01,274 --> 00:04:02,041
come to me anytime.

63
00:04:03,409 --> 00:04:03,843
My door

64
00:04:04,510 --> 00:04:05,845
will always be open to you.

65
00:04:07,880 --> 00:04:08,448
Thank you, President Wang.

66
00:04:09,349 --> 00:04:09,716
Have some tea.

67
00:04:17,123 --> 00:04:17,724
This is so good.

68
00:04:17,724 --> 00:04:18,691
I need another one.

69
00:04:18,691 --> 00:04:19,325
Dr. Fang,

70
00:04:19,325 --> 00:04:20,560
eat less. Aren't you dieting?

71
00:04:20,793 --> 00:04:21,527
I just like eating.

72
00:04:21,561 --> 00:04:23,429
Who ordered all this afternoon tea?

73
00:04:24,364 --> 00:04:25,398
Director Lin.

74
00:04:25,765 --> 00:04:26,432
It just arrived.

75
00:04:27,367 --> 00:04:27,934
Lin Yi.

76
00:04:28,968 --> 00:04:30,169
Everyone in our department

77
00:04:30,236 --> 00:04:31,838
is going to be fattened up by Director Lin.

78
00:04:32,639 --> 00:04:34,507
I never dreamed

79
00:04:34,674 --> 00:04:35,875
that one day our ICU

80
00:04:36,009 --> 00:04:37,310
would get treats

81
00:04:37,343 --> 00:04:38,344
from Cardiac Surgery.

82
00:04:39,646 --> 00:04:40,513
No wonder.

83
00:04:40,647 --> 00:04:41,748
I was wondering why Director Lin

84
00:04:41,848 --> 00:04:43,049
added me on WeChat last time.

85
00:04:43,783 --> 00:04:45,585
We recruited Dr. Fang

86
00:04:45,785 --> 00:04:46,719
and got

87
00:04:46,786 --> 00:04:47,787
a Cardiac Surgery expert as a free bonus.

88
00:04:48,254 --> 00:04:48,855
What a bargain.

89
00:04:48,988 --> 00:04:49,422
Exactly.

90
00:04:49,689 --> 00:04:50,990
In the past, Cardiac Surgery consults

91
00:04:51,124 --> 00:04:52,158
had to follow the whole procedure.

92
00:04:52,425 --> 00:04:53,893
Director Lin was busy operating

93
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:54,627
and rarely came.

94
00:04:54,794 --> 00:04:55,528
Now it's great.

95
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:57,063
We make one phone call,

96
00:04:57,330 --> 00:04:57,864
and Director Lin

97
00:04:58,631 --> 00:04:59,565
teleports over.

98
00:05:01,534 --> 00:05:02,035
Dr. Fang,

99
00:05:02,568 --> 00:05:03,603
coffee, milk tea,

100
00:05:03,636 --> 00:05:04,270
or a sandwich?

101
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:04,904
Which do you want?

102
00:05:06,205 --> 00:05:07,974
I'm not eating yet. You guys go ahead.

103
00:05:09,008 --> 00:05:10,109
Then we won't hold back.

104
00:05:10,343 --> 00:05:10,810
Come on.

105
00:05:10,810 --> 00:05:11,811
It'll be gone soon.

106
00:05:11,844 --> 00:05:12,745
I'll finish it all.

107
00:05:12,879 --> 00:05:13,713
My favorite. Give me one.

108
00:05:14,881 --> 00:05:15,748
I want a milk tea.

109
00:05:16,115 --> 00:05:16,449
This one.

110
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:17,550
Coffee.

111
00:05:19,452 --> 00:05:19,919
Coffee, right?

112
00:05:31,264 --> 00:05:32,131
Thanks for the milk tea.

113
00:05:37,370 --> 00:05:38,871
Why are you so free lately?

114
00:05:48,648 --> 00:05:49,916
I've stopped traveling for outside surgeries.

115
00:05:50,683 --> 00:05:51,284
No more business trips.

116
00:05:52,719 --> 00:05:53,453
I've quit drinking.

117
00:05:53,953 --> 00:05:54,787
And gambling.

118
00:06:00,927 --> 00:06:01,527
Why?

119
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:17,276
I want to find the old Lin Yi again.

120
00:06:26,085 --> 00:06:26,686
Is it good?

121
00:06:26,919 --> 00:06:28,287
Yes. Aren't you having any? Try some.

122
00:06:43,169 --> 00:06:43,836
Dr. Fang.

123
00:06:44,837 --> 00:06:45,605
How did you find out?

124
00:06:48,074 --> 00:06:48,608
Sister Mo.

125
00:06:49,408 --> 00:06:50,510
Didn't the cafeteria's seafood casserole place

126
00:06:50,543 --> 00:06:51,511
stop selling it?

127
00:06:51,911 --> 00:06:53,045
This isn't from our cafeteria.

128
00:06:53,846 --> 00:06:55,014
Have you tried

129
00:06:55,748 --> 00:06:56,349
the malatang place by the entrance?

130
00:06:56,549 --> 00:06:57,917
Yes, I go there often.

131
00:06:58,751 --> 00:07:00,286
They've started selling seafood casseroles.

132
00:07:00,853 --> 00:07:01,521
Lingling brought it for me.

133
00:07:02,355 --> 00:07:02,922
I brought it.

134
00:07:04,357 --> 00:07:05,591
It really is pretty good.

135
00:07:05,591 --> 00:07:05,925
Look at her.

136
00:07:06,692 --> 00:07:07,593
She can't stop eating.

137
00:07:13,132 --> 00:07:13,566
Boss,

138
00:07:13,966 --> 00:07:15,168
one seafood casserole, please.

139
00:07:16,235 --> 00:07:16,936
Uncle Feng.

140
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:17,837
Sorry.

141
00:07:18,037 --> 00:07:18,971
We're sold out of the seafood casserole.

142
00:07:22,074 --> 00:07:23,042
Why are you here?

143
00:07:23,743 --> 00:07:24,143
I...

144
00:07:25,912 --> 00:07:27,847
I came for malatang.

145
00:07:28,948 --> 00:07:29,515
Boss,

146
00:07:29,649 --> 00:07:30,516
add another portion

147
00:07:30,783 --> 00:07:31,651
of shrimp for me.

148
00:07:35,388 --> 00:07:35,955
Boss.

149
00:07:36,589 --> 00:07:37,390
Boss, someone's looking for you.

150
00:07:39,358 --> 00:07:40,126
You want shrimp, right?

151
00:07:40,493 --> 00:07:42,762
Xiao Lin, do you still have shrimp?

152
00:07:43,529 --> 00:07:44,130
Add one portion for him.

153
00:07:46,365 --> 00:07:47,567
You're cooking here?

154
00:07:52,805 --> 00:07:54,841
Didn't the hospital cafeteria's seafood casserole stall

155
00:07:55,107 --> 00:07:55,975
close down?

156
00:07:56,943 --> 00:07:57,844
I just thought...

157
00:07:59,011 --> 00:07:59,645
I thought

158
00:08:00,613 --> 00:08:01,480
someone liked eating it.

159
00:08:02,615 --> 00:08:03,015
So

160
00:08:03,449 --> 00:08:04,250
I started making it here.

161
00:08:12,291 --> 00:08:14,594
But it's sold out, right?

162
00:08:19,131 --> 00:08:20,066
Fish-ball casserole.

163
00:08:23,069 --> 00:08:25,071
Everything else is sold out,

164
00:08:26,038 --> 00:08:27,773
but I stocked lots of fish balls.

165
00:08:42,722 --> 00:08:43,322
How does it taste?

166
00:08:44,023 --> 00:08:44,891
Not bad.

167
00:08:44,991 --> 00:08:45,524
Really?

168
00:08:47,159 --> 00:08:47,760
Originally,

169
00:08:48,928 --> 00:08:50,830
I just wanted to test

170
00:08:50,863 --> 00:08:51,597
how it tasted.

171
00:08:52,632 --> 00:08:54,734
Once I got the seafood casserole right,

172
00:08:55,334 --> 00:08:56,435
I planned to bring it to you.

173
00:08:58,004 --> 00:08:58,905
But I didn't expect

174
00:08:59,372 --> 00:09:01,040
it to be a success right away.

175
00:09:01,507 --> 00:09:02,642
It all sold out.

176
00:09:03,109 --> 00:09:04,277
Seriously?

177
00:09:04,310 --> 00:09:04,844
Yes.

178
00:09:04,877 --> 00:09:05,811
The owner even asked me

179
00:09:05,845 --> 00:09:07,046
whether I had a secret recipe.

180
00:09:16,289 --> 00:09:17,390
Aren't you busy today?

181
00:09:18,491 --> 00:09:19,158
No.

182
00:09:19,191 --> 00:09:20,593
I only have a little work in the OR.

183
00:09:21,994 --> 00:09:23,229
Operating is already exhausting.

184
00:09:23,729 --> 00:09:24,563
Not at all.

185
00:09:25,665 --> 00:09:26,532
It can't compare with you.

186
00:09:28,134 --> 00:09:29,535
You run between the ICU

187
00:09:29,602 --> 00:09:31,103
and the Heart Center every day.

188
00:09:31,837 --> 00:09:32,805
You work much harder.

189
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:35,107
I'm okay.

190
00:09:44,884 --> 00:09:45,585
You're always like that.

191
00:09:46,786 --> 00:09:48,254
No matter how tired or overwhelmed you are,

192
00:09:50,623 --> 00:09:51,591
you say you're fine.

193
00:09:52,224 --> 00:09:52,825
Nothing's wrong.

194
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:55,728
I was really foolish before.

195
00:09:59,632 --> 00:10:00,800
I actually believed you weren't tired.

196
00:10:02,835 --> 00:10:04,036
But now I know

197
00:10:08,474 --> 00:10:09,108
you've been carrying everything

198
00:10:09,175 --> 00:10:10,509
on your own, in silence.

199
00:10:14,113 --> 00:10:14,947
You get tired too.

200
00:10:16,682 --> 00:10:17,583
You run out of power too.

201
00:10:26,792 --> 00:10:27,293
Xiaoran.

202
00:10:29,729 --> 00:10:30,629
The next time

203
00:10:31,831 --> 00:10:33,232
you run out of power,

204
00:10:36,836 --> 00:10:37,903
you can come to me.

205
00:10:40,873 --> 00:10:41,774
What for?

206
00:10:46,245 --> 00:10:46,846
Come to me...

207
00:10:48,347 --> 00:10:49,949
and I'll make you seafood casserole.

208
00:10:50,116 --> 00:10:51,183
I make it so well.

209
00:10:53,119 --> 00:10:54,453
Or fish-ball casserole.

210
00:10:55,888 --> 00:10:56,389
Anything works.

211
00:10:57,289 --> 00:10:58,691
Whatever you want, I'll make it into a casserole.

212
00:10:58,924 --> 00:10:59,592
Casserole everything.

213
00:11:12,571 --> 00:11:13,005
Anyway,

214
00:11:13,906 --> 00:11:15,107
I'll make it just for you.

215
00:11:29,288 --> 00:11:30,156
I know.

216
00:11:30,890 --> 00:11:31,757
I've been taking

217
00:11:31,757 --> 00:11:33,192
targeted drugs for pulmonary hypertension for months.

218
00:11:34,126 --> 00:11:35,695
My previous doctor said

219
00:11:36,128 --> 00:11:37,763
I improved after the medication

220
00:11:39,031 --> 00:11:40,733
and had reached a window for surgery.

221
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,802
But the doctors here

222
00:11:42,968 --> 00:11:44,704
don't recommend surgery.

223
00:11:44,904 --> 00:11:45,638
Cardiology performed

224
00:11:45,638 --> 00:11:46,806
a cardiac catheterization.

225
00:11:47,073 --> 00:11:48,240
They found her pulmonary vascular resistance

226
00:11:48,307 --> 00:11:49,408
was already borderline.

227
00:11:49,842 --> 00:11:51,143
If we repair it now,

228
00:11:51,310 --> 00:11:52,211
there's insufficient evidence of benefit.

229
00:11:53,079 --> 00:11:54,480
I'll wait for you at the hospital.

230
00:11:54,914 --> 00:11:55,848
Let's talk in person.

231
00:11:57,516 --> 00:11:57,783
Okay.

232
00:11:58,150 --> 00:11:58,584
Bye.

233
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:01,921
Excuse me.

234
00:12:04,323 --> 00:12:05,191
I'm Sheng Nian,

235
00:12:05,224 --> 00:12:06,592
Director of Cardiac Surgery at the Heart Center.

236
00:12:09,295 --> 00:12:10,730
Hello, Director Sheng.

237
00:12:11,230 --> 00:12:11,664
Hello.

238
00:12:18,070 --> 00:12:18,571
Here, have some water.

239
00:12:19,038 --> 00:12:19,972
All right. Thank you.

240
00:12:21,273 --> 00:12:22,174
Thank you, Director Sheng.

241
00:12:29,782 --> 00:12:30,616
Director Sheng,

242
00:12:31,750 --> 00:12:33,986
Director Zhou and Director Lin said

243
00:12:34,453 --> 00:12:35,921
after the VSD repair,

244
00:12:36,689 --> 00:12:39,291
I might develop acute right heart failure,

245
00:12:39,925 --> 00:12:41,127
so they don't recommend surgery.

246
00:12:42,561 --> 00:12:43,195
They're not wrong.

247
00:12:44,363 --> 00:12:45,131
But

248
00:12:45,831 --> 00:12:47,233
there's another surgical option

249
00:12:48,134 --> 00:12:49,969
that differs from the conventional one.

250
00:12:50,769 --> 00:12:52,004
There's another way.

251
00:12:53,606 --> 00:12:54,840
That Professor Yang—

252
00:12:55,207 --> 00:12:56,642
you're competing with him

253
00:12:57,209 --> 00:12:58,711
for chair of the Heart Failure Association.

254
00:12:59,311 --> 00:13:00,479
You need to pull out something big.

255
00:13:00,913 --> 00:13:02,414
When it comes to Cardiac Surgery procedures,

256
00:13:02,882 --> 00:13:04,016
in terms of technical level,

257
00:13:04,483 --> 00:13:05,951
there isn't really any objective measure.

258
00:13:06,652 --> 00:13:08,154
If you just take

259
00:13:08,187 --> 00:13:09,255
a routine procedure

260
00:13:10,723 --> 00:13:11,924
and do it again, how much attention can it draw?

261
00:13:12,391 --> 00:13:14,393
You need a chance to flex your muscles.

262
00:13:16,295 --> 00:13:17,830
I won't close the hole completely.

263
00:13:18,430 --> 00:13:19,999
When repairing your VSD,

264
00:13:19,999 --> 00:13:20,633
I will

265
00:13:20,866 --> 00:13:21,867
create a valved opening

266
00:13:22,001 --> 00:13:22,868
in the patch,

267
00:13:23,135 --> 00:13:23,769
leaving some room.

268
00:13:24,236 --> 00:13:26,071
That way, we avoid another operation.

269
00:13:27,072 --> 00:13:27,807
Director Sheng,

270
00:13:27,907 --> 00:13:28,841
have you performed

271
00:13:28,841 --> 00:13:29,608
this kind of surgery before?

272
00:13:29,975 --> 00:13:30,376
Of course.

273
00:13:31,143 --> 00:13:31,911
Several cases.

274
00:13:32,912 --> 00:13:33,913
And based on

275
00:13:33,946 --> 00:13:35,047
those previous cases,

276
00:13:35,114 --> 00:13:36,348
I can make further improvements

277
00:13:37,082 --> 00:13:37,516
and strive

278
00:13:37,716 --> 00:13:39,351
to make the valve even better.

279
00:13:40,252 --> 00:13:40,920
Director Sheng,

280
00:13:41,187 --> 00:13:42,454
how did

281
00:13:42,588 --> 00:13:44,323
the patients in those previous cases

282
00:13:44,757 --> 00:13:45,991
recover?

283
00:13:47,693 --> 00:13:49,862
If I have this surgery,

284
00:13:50,262 --> 00:13:51,363
in your experience,

285
00:13:51,864 --> 00:13:53,566
will I be able to move around normally

286
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:55,734
by this time next year?

287
00:13:56,635 --> 00:13:57,269
Of course.

288
00:13:57,836 --> 00:13:59,004
I can't promise

289
00:13:59,104 --> 00:13:59,972
you'll live to a hundred,

290
00:14:00,773 --> 00:14:01,473
but one year

291
00:14:02,107 --> 00:14:02,975
should be absolutely fine.

292
00:14:03,842 --> 00:14:05,211
Among the patients who had this surgery,

293
00:14:05,211 --> 00:14:06,078
the oldest

294
00:14:06,245 --> 00:14:07,746
was discharged two and a half years ago

295
00:14:08,214 --> 00:14:08,881
and recovered very well.

296
00:14:09,882 --> 00:14:11,150
She called me just a few days ago

297
00:14:11,550 --> 00:14:13,485
and said she was traveling in Yunnan with her husband.

298
00:14:15,588 --> 00:14:16,522
I've always believed

299
00:14:17,489 --> 00:14:18,324
that after surgery,

300
00:14:18,557 --> 00:14:19,525
patients shouldn't merely survive.

301
00:14:19,892 --> 00:14:20,826
They should live well,

302
00:14:21,227 --> 00:14:22,161
and with dignity,

303
00:14:23,329 --> 00:14:24,530
not like now,

304
00:14:24,864 --> 00:14:25,598
out of breath with every movement.

305
00:14:26,999 --> 00:14:27,566
Think about it.

306
00:14:28,634 --> 00:14:29,969
As long as the VSD remains,

307
00:14:30,269 --> 00:14:31,203
the root cause remains.

308
00:14:32,171 --> 00:14:34,073
The dose of targeted drugs keeps increasing,

309
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:36,442
while the effect keeps weakening.

310
00:14:36,976 --> 00:14:38,844
And the drugs aren't cheap.

311
00:14:40,246 --> 00:14:40,613
Exactly.

312
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:42,815
Right now,

313
00:14:42,915 --> 00:14:44,350
we pay over two thousand yuan a month out of pocket.

314
00:14:46,919 --> 00:14:47,887
To be honest,

315
00:14:48,687 --> 00:14:50,155
this operation is very high-risk.

316
00:14:51,223 --> 00:14:53,192
Most doctors won't even suggest it,

317
00:14:53,425 --> 00:14:54,360
much less perform it.

318
00:14:55,394 --> 00:14:57,730
These days, people talk about defensive medicine—

319
00:14:58,030 --> 00:14:59,598
better to avoid trouble.

320
00:15:00,432 --> 00:15:01,867
But look at my specialist clinic.

321
00:15:02,368 --> 00:15:03,168
It's fully booked every month.

322
00:15:03,502 --> 00:15:04,670
I can barely finish all my surgeries.

323
00:15:05,304 --> 00:15:05,871
That's why

324
00:15:06,305 --> 00:15:07,172
I have the confidence

325
00:15:07,706 --> 00:15:08,908
to take on this challenge.

326
00:15:10,209 --> 00:15:10,876
At the same time,

327
00:15:11,477 --> 00:15:12,645
I don't want to see you

328
00:15:12,945 --> 00:15:13,812
lose hope.

329
00:15:16,081 --> 00:15:16,548
Of course,

330
00:15:17,116 --> 00:15:18,517
I'm only offering you

331
00:15:18,884 --> 00:15:19,785
another choice.

332
00:15:20,986 --> 00:15:21,787
Whether to take it

333
00:15:22,354 --> 00:15:22,888
is up to you.

334
00:15:28,427 --> 00:15:29,395
Thank you, Director Sheng.

335
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:35,734
Director Lin.

336
00:15:36,735 --> 00:15:37,403
Director Lin.

337
00:15:41,473 --> 00:15:41,907
Why are you

338
00:15:41,907 --> 00:15:42,775
on the Cardiac Surgery ward?

339
00:15:44,843 --> 00:15:47,212
I'm transferring here for surgery.

340
00:15:48,447 --> 00:15:49,114
What surgery?

341
00:15:49,882 --> 00:15:51,750
A repair

342
00:15:51,784 --> 00:15:52,851
with a valved patch.

343
00:15:55,187 --> 00:15:55,721
Who's operating?

344
00:15:56,588 --> 00:15:58,390
Director Sheng Nian from Cardiac Surgery.

345
00:15:58,557 --> 00:15:59,625
You Xiaoli's bed

346
00:16:00,025 --> 00:16:00,426
is ready.

347
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:01,360
Director Lin,

348
00:16:01,427 --> 00:16:02,227
I'll go over first.

349
00:16:05,931 --> 00:16:06,632
What's going on?

350
00:16:07,766 --> 00:16:08,567
I don't know when

351
00:16:08,567 --> 00:16:09,268
they met Director Sheng.

352
00:16:09,868 --> 00:16:10,903
She insisted on transferring to Cardiac Surgery.

353
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:11,770
Xiao Ye couldn't persuade her.

354
00:16:12,037 --> 00:16:12,805
I only just found out too.

355
00:16:12,838 --> 00:16:13,772
Okay. Thank you.

356
00:16:13,772 --> 00:16:14,239
Put your things down.

357
00:16:14,239 --> 00:16:15,307
Let me help you onto the bed.

358
00:16:18,844 --> 00:16:19,812
Pulmonary hypertension

359
00:16:19,878 --> 00:16:21,647
is a world-class challenge.

360
00:16:22,214 --> 00:16:23,349
If surgery proves

361
00:16:23,349 --> 00:16:24,216
effective,

362
00:16:24,583 --> 00:16:25,517
we must publicize it properly.

363
00:16:26,051 --> 00:16:27,286
I've even thought of the slogan:

364
00:16:27,886 --> 00:16:29,788
"New Hope for Patients with Pulmonary Hypertension."

365
00:16:30,756 --> 00:16:31,156
Director,

366
00:16:31,523 --> 00:16:32,291
this is hugely significant.

367
00:16:32,758 --> 00:16:33,192
Exactly.

368
00:16:39,264 --> 00:16:39,932
Why did you suddenly decide

369
00:16:39,965 --> 00:16:40,966
to operate on You Xiaoli?

370
00:16:41,633 --> 00:16:42,267
Is there a problem?

371
00:16:43,068 --> 00:16:44,036
Her current condition

372
00:16:44,136 --> 00:16:45,504
doesn't meet the criteria for surgery at all.

373
00:16:45,904 --> 00:16:47,239
Whether you repair the VSD

374
00:16:47,473 --> 00:16:48,240
or use a valved patch,

375
00:16:48,374 --> 00:16:49,375
it has no meaning.

376
00:16:49,675 --> 00:16:50,909
How is it meaningless?

377
00:16:51,543 --> 00:16:52,277
Several of my patients

378
00:16:52,277 --> 00:16:53,212
are alive and doing well.

379
00:16:54,079 --> 00:16:55,314
I've followed them continuously.

380
00:16:55,881 --> 00:16:56,882
I know my own patients.

381
00:16:57,049 --> 00:16:57,783
The risk is too high.

382
00:16:57,783 --> 00:16:58,550
Every patient's situation

383
00:16:58,550 --> 00:16:59,385
is different.

384
00:16:59,752 --> 00:17:00,719
In women, pulmonary artery pressure

385
00:17:00,719 --> 00:17:01,887
is inherently harder to reduce than in men.

386
00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:02,488
Her pulmonary-to-systemic

387
00:17:02,488 --> 00:17:03,055
flow ratio

388
00:17:03,055 --> 00:17:03,555
is 1.5.

389
00:17:04,022 --> 00:17:05,190
Her pulmonary hypertension is irreversible.

390
00:17:05,758 --> 00:17:06,959
She's already taken targeted medication

391
00:17:06,992 --> 00:17:07,993
and it has come down somewhat.

392
00:17:08,227 --> 00:17:09,028
You call it irreversible,

393
00:17:09,094 --> 00:17:10,262
but that conclusion is too absolute.

394
00:17:10,729 --> 00:17:12,131
I believe there's still some chance

395
00:17:12,264 --> 00:17:12,965
it can be reversed.

396
00:17:13,165 --> 00:17:13,766
How much?

397
00:17:18,070 --> 00:17:19,471
What do you think

398
00:17:19,505 --> 00:17:20,105
the success rate is?

399
00:17:25,277 --> 00:17:25,811
Lin Yi,

400
00:17:26,678 --> 00:17:27,846
watch your tone.

401
00:17:28,347 --> 00:17:29,214
At Dongli Hospital,

402
00:17:29,248 --> 00:17:30,549
no subordinate department member

403
00:17:30,582 --> 00:17:32,050
gets to question a superior's surgical plan.

404
00:17:32,284 --> 00:17:32,951
In front of a patient,

405
00:17:32,951 --> 00:17:34,119
there are no superiors or subordinates,

406
00:17:34,787 --> 00:17:36,188
only the best treatment plan.

407
00:17:37,256 --> 00:17:38,957
What surgery isn't risky?

408
00:17:39,358 --> 00:17:40,359
Any new technique

409
00:17:40,359 --> 00:17:40,793
has some experimental nature

410
00:17:40,993 --> 00:17:42,027
at the beginning.

411
00:17:42,361 --> 00:17:42,895
Every patient

412
00:17:42,928 --> 00:17:43,796
is a living person,

413
00:17:43,896 --> 00:17:44,596
not a lab subject

414
00:17:44,630 --> 00:17:45,397
in your experiment.

415
00:17:58,143 --> 00:17:58,510
Hello?

416
00:18:00,012 --> 00:18:00,345
Okay.

417
00:18:01,313 --> 00:18:01,814
I'm coming right away.

418
00:18:03,415 --> 00:18:04,216
Director,

419
00:18:04,650 --> 00:18:05,984
the ER just admitted a new patient.

420
00:18:06,051 --> 00:18:06,919
The situation is urgent.

421
00:18:06,985 --> 00:18:07,719
They're going to the OR now.

422
00:18:08,153 --> 00:18:09,087
We'll head over first.

423
00:18:09,321 --> 00:18:10,155
My meeting isn't over.

424
00:18:14,193 --> 00:18:15,127
Can the OR not function

425
00:18:15,160 --> 00:18:15,894
without you two?

426
00:18:24,103 --> 00:18:25,404
If you think the operation can't be done,

427
00:18:25,871 --> 00:18:26,705
that's your problem.

428
00:18:27,973 --> 00:18:29,007
You have no say here.

429
00:18:30,175 --> 00:18:30,542
Get out.

430
00:18:32,144 --> 00:18:32,478
And another thing—

431
00:18:33,245 --> 00:18:34,012
I'm warning you,

432
00:18:34,913 --> 00:18:35,814
don't pull the same trick again.

433
00:18:48,026 --> 00:18:48,560
Continue the meeting.

434
00:19:01,607 --> 00:19:02,508
Why not go to the president?

435
00:19:04,276 --> 00:19:05,144
It won't help.

436
00:19:05,644 --> 00:19:07,045
Director Sheng now insists

437
00:19:07,246 --> 00:19:08,247
he's confident about the surgery.

438
00:19:08,814 --> 00:19:10,015
There's no point talking to the president.

439
00:19:11,083 --> 00:19:12,451
And the key is You Xiaoli.

440
00:19:12,684 --> 00:19:13,352
As long as she insists

441
00:19:13,385 --> 00:19:14,386
on having the operation,

442
00:19:14,920 --> 00:19:16,121
there's nothing we can do.

443
00:19:17,022 --> 00:19:17,923
Then try persuading her again.

444
00:19:19,591 --> 00:19:20,959
You know how stubborn she is.

445
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:23,095
We've tried so many times.

446
00:19:23,128 --> 00:19:23,629
She never listened.

447
00:19:24,263 --> 00:19:25,531
She probably won't now either.

448
00:19:38,110 --> 00:19:38,677
Find Xiaoran.

449
00:19:42,614 --> 00:19:43,482
The core issue now

450
00:19:43,515 --> 00:19:44,950
is You Xiaoli's own wishes.

451
00:19:46,151 --> 00:19:47,486
We've explained the good and the bad,

452
00:19:47,719 --> 00:19:48,453
but she still won't listen.

453
00:19:48,954 --> 00:19:49,988
That's why we thought of asking you.

454
00:19:51,757 --> 00:19:53,125
If she's confirmed

455
00:19:53,158 --> 00:19:54,493
to be fully informed,

456
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:56,128
then in a moment I'll

457
00:19:56,295 --> 00:19:57,796
ask why she's so determined.

458
00:20:00,832 --> 00:20:01,233
Come in.

459
00:20:02,534 --> 00:20:03,135
Director Zhou.

460
00:20:03,468 --> 00:20:04,102
Director Lin.

461
00:20:04,269 --> 00:20:04,836
Dr. Fang.

462
00:20:07,239 --> 00:20:07,873
Where's your mother?

463
00:20:08,507 --> 00:20:10,008
I'm here in her place.

464
00:20:12,878 --> 00:20:13,412
Have a seat first.

465
00:20:15,681 --> 00:20:16,014
Here.

466
00:20:17,149 --> 00:20:17,716
Thank you.

467
00:20:21,353 --> 00:20:22,721
Regarding your mother's surgery,

468
00:20:22,854 --> 00:20:24,523
we'd still like to talk with her again.

469
00:20:25,290 --> 00:20:25,891
I know

470
00:20:25,958 --> 00:20:27,192
you're all acting in her best interests.

471
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:29,361
But she's already decided.

472
00:20:30,562 --> 00:20:31,863
And I'll support her having the surgery.

473
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:36,868
Why are you both so determined?

474
00:20:40,439 --> 00:20:43,408
My mother is someone who deeply loves life

475
00:20:43,809 --> 00:20:44,843
and freedom.

476
00:20:45,844 --> 00:20:47,112
She always notices

477
00:20:47,479 --> 00:20:48,013
things in life

478
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:49,414
that other people overlook.

479
00:20:50,048 --> 00:20:51,783
She loves walking around,

480
00:20:52,117 --> 00:20:52,884
being close to nature.

481
00:20:53,852 --> 00:20:54,853
But now,

482
00:20:55,354 --> 00:20:56,455
most of the time,

483
00:20:56,688 --> 00:20:58,023
she can only stay at home.

484
00:20:58,523 --> 00:20:59,424
She can't go anywhere.

485
00:21:01,793 --> 00:21:02,761
She no longer has

486
00:21:02,794 --> 00:21:03,996
any quality of life.

487
00:21:04,396 --> 00:21:05,764
I know she's suffering.

488
00:21:06,231 --> 00:21:07,966
And she has

489
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:08,967
one greatest wish:

490
00:21:09,401 --> 00:21:10,502
next year,

491
00:21:10,969 --> 00:21:12,904
she wants to walk onto the stage

492
00:21:13,472 --> 00:21:15,707
without support, like any ordinary mother,

493
00:21:17,175 --> 00:21:18,310
all by herself

494
00:21:18,543 --> 00:21:19,911
to attend my coming-of-age ceremony.

495
00:21:20,612 --> 00:21:22,547
That's the promise between us.

496
00:21:26,251 --> 00:21:26,852
Linlang.

497
00:21:28,186 --> 00:21:29,087
Whether to have surgery,

498
00:21:29,087 --> 00:21:30,122
we can only offer recommendations.

499
00:21:30,956 --> 00:21:31,490
Of course, ultimately

500
00:21:31,523 --> 00:21:32,891
the decision is yours.

501
00:21:34,393 --> 00:21:35,327
But I want to know:

502
00:21:36,495 --> 00:21:37,596
did Director Sheng clearly explain

503
00:21:37,629 --> 00:21:38,363
the risks and benefits

504
00:21:38,530 --> 00:21:39,798
of the operation?

505
00:21:40,732 --> 00:21:41,566
Director Sheng explained everything

506
00:21:41,566 --> 00:21:42,334
very clearly.

507
00:21:42,934 --> 00:21:44,603
He said the surgery is high-risk

508
00:21:45,003 --> 00:21:45,837
and extremely challenging.

509
00:21:46,972 --> 00:21:47,973
But like me,

510
00:21:48,407 --> 00:21:48,907
he understands my mother

511
00:21:48,907 --> 00:21:50,275
and why she wants the operation.

512
00:21:51,610 --> 00:21:52,911
She doesn't want regrets.

513
00:21:53,945 --> 00:21:55,280
And I don't want her to have regrets either.

514
00:21:57,883 --> 00:21:58,583
She wants

515
00:21:58,984 --> 00:22:00,152
to live with dignity

516
00:22:01,253 --> 00:22:02,487
and quality,

517
00:22:03,889 --> 00:22:04,956
even if it's only for one year.

518
00:22:05,957 --> 00:22:06,758
I support her.

519
00:22:07,993 --> 00:22:09,194
Just like

520
00:22:09,194 --> 00:22:10,362
the little animals in my mother's books.

521
00:22:10,929 --> 00:22:13,031
Those tiny friends she writes about

522
00:22:13,565 --> 00:22:14,566
are wild species

523
00:22:14,599 --> 00:22:16,201
we usually overlook.

524
00:22:16,835 --> 00:22:17,936
Because my mother says

525
00:22:18,270 --> 00:22:19,237
even the smallest life

526
00:22:19,471 --> 00:22:20,972
can live wonderfully

527
00:22:21,973 --> 00:22:23,008
and deserves to be seen.

528
00:22:27,079 --> 00:22:29,314
Xiaoxiao and her friends

529
00:22:29,648 --> 00:22:32,250
attended the mayflies' grand feast.

530
00:22:33,051 --> 00:22:35,687
Mayflies have extremely short lives.

531
00:22:36,488 --> 00:22:37,789
Adult mayflies

532
00:22:37,956 --> 00:22:39,758
live only a few hours,

533
00:22:40,392 --> 00:22:42,294
at most a few days.

534
00:22:42,794 --> 00:22:45,997
But as they dance in the sunlight,

535
00:22:46,431 --> 00:22:48,467
they still have beautiful wings

536
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:50,202
and graceful forms.

537
00:22:50,669 --> 00:22:52,270
That's why the ancients said:

538
00:22:52,804 --> 00:22:55,006
"Born at dawn and dead by dusk,

539
00:22:55,607 --> 00:22:58,210
yet adorned with wings."

540
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:01,146
They are born for love.

541
00:23:01,813 --> 00:23:03,348
Though so tiny,

542
00:23:03,915 --> 00:23:06,551
they live with dazzling brilliance.

543
00:23:10,455 --> 00:23:11,256
If both the patient and family

544
00:23:11,256 --> 00:23:12,524
are this determined,

545
00:23:13,291 --> 00:23:14,226
we have no way

546
00:23:14,292 --> 00:23:15,127
to stop them.

547
00:23:17,028 --> 00:23:17,696
Then what do we do?

548
00:23:20,198 --> 00:23:21,366
Hope Director Sheng's surgery

549
00:23:21,366 --> 00:23:21,933
works a miracle.

550
00:23:24,569 --> 00:23:25,403
That's all we can do.

551
00:23:29,174 --> 00:23:29,841
Sorry

552
00:23:32,144 --> 00:23:33,044
you came for nothing.

553
00:23:34,413 --> 00:23:36,148
It's okay. We had to try.

554
00:23:41,052 --> 00:23:41,987
I have another surgery shortly.

555
00:23:51,129 --> 00:23:52,364
He had a huge argument with Director Sheng

556
00:23:53,165 --> 00:23:54,332
over You Xiaoli.

557
00:23:56,001 --> 00:23:57,169
So they really did fight.

558
00:24:00,372 --> 00:24:01,106
I feel like he's

559
00:24:01,106 --> 00:24:02,507
gradually becoming his old self again.

560
00:24:03,909 --> 00:24:04,910
Focused entirely on the patient,

561
00:24:05,744 --> 00:24:06,845
unable to tolerate anything wrong.

562
00:24:11,483 --> 00:24:13,084
I want to find the old Lin Yi again.

563
00:24:18,390 --> 00:24:19,424
How about you?

564
00:24:19,791 --> 00:24:20,392
How are things

565
00:24:20,392 --> 00:24:20,926
in the general ICU?

566
00:24:21,726 --> 00:24:22,794
Smoother than I expected.

567
00:24:23,328 --> 00:24:24,563
Director Ji has been very supportive.

568
00:24:25,463 --> 00:24:27,399
Every day brings new challenges,

569
00:24:27,766 --> 00:24:28,667
and it feels rewarding.

570
00:24:30,068 --> 00:24:30,502
That's good.

571
00:24:31,703 --> 00:24:32,504
I'm going to the general ICU

572
00:24:32,504 --> 00:24:33,071
to take a look,

573
00:24:33,071 --> 00:24:33,905
then head back.

574
00:24:36,107 --> 00:24:36,508
Right?

575
00:24:36,575 --> 00:24:37,275
Bed 19, right?

576
00:24:37,342 --> 00:24:37,909
Here. Here. Here.

577
00:24:38,009 --> 00:24:38,510
Here, Bed 19.

578
00:24:38,543 --> 00:24:39,444
Quickly.

579
00:24:40,445 --> 00:24:40,912
Xiaoli.

580
00:24:40,946 --> 00:24:42,614
Big Sister, Second Sister, Third Sister.

581
00:24:42,814 --> 00:24:43,648
The child fell asleep.

582
00:24:44,416 --> 00:24:45,317
She's exhausted.

583
00:24:46,585 --> 00:24:47,686
I thought you wouldn't arrive

584
00:24:47,719 --> 00:24:48,687
until this afternoon.

585
00:24:48,887 --> 00:24:49,888
Your second sister was anxious.

586
00:24:49,888 --> 00:24:50,489
At five in the morning,

587
00:24:50,522 --> 00:24:51,323
she called me

588
00:24:51,423 --> 00:24:52,224
and rushed me over.

589
00:24:52,624 --> 00:24:53,191
Of course I was anxious.

590
00:24:53,191 --> 00:24:53,959
I didn't sleep all night.

591
00:24:53,959 --> 00:24:54,793
Keep your voice down.

592
00:24:55,227 --> 00:24:55,894
What?

593
00:24:56,027 --> 00:24:56,528
Xiaoli.

594
00:24:57,095 --> 00:24:57,729
What do you mean by this?

595
00:24:57,762 --> 00:24:58,797
You only told us now?

596
00:24:59,598 --> 00:25:00,599
You've gotten bold, haven't you?

597
00:25:00,632 --> 00:25:01,666
You're trying to bear everything alone again.

598
00:25:01,833 --> 00:25:02,801
All right, all right.

599
00:25:02,834 --> 00:25:03,668
The child's sleeping.

600
00:25:03,802 --> 00:25:04,436
Okay, okay.

601
00:25:07,172 --> 00:25:07,906
She's awake.

602
00:25:10,108 --> 00:25:10,742
Linlang.

603
00:25:11,243 --> 00:25:11,810
You're awake.

604
00:25:12,077 --> 00:25:13,545
Look who's here.

605
00:25:16,214 --> 00:25:16,882
Auntie.

606
00:25:17,349 --> 00:25:17,949
Second Auntie.

607
00:25:19,184 --> 00:25:19,918
Third Auntie.

608
00:25:22,520 --> 00:25:23,388
You've worked hard.

609
00:25:23,955 --> 00:25:24,756
You've all lost weight.

610
00:25:26,992 --> 00:25:28,293
You even have dark circles.

611
00:25:29,494 --> 00:25:30,028
Big Sister.

612
00:25:30,528 --> 00:25:31,663
All right. Don't cry.

613
00:25:31,963 --> 00:25:32,931
Don't cry. We're all here.

614
00:25:33,064 --> 00:25:34,165
You don't need to be afraid now.

615
00:25:36,535 --> 00:25:37,035
Ms. You,

616
00:25:37,769 --> 00:25:38,970
the civil trust agreement

617
00:25:39,237 --> 00:25:40,572
and the designated guardianship agreement

618
00:25:40,772 --> 00:25:42,040
have all been signed by the three of them.

619
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:43,275
The three of them will jointly supervise

620
00:25:43,441 --> 00:25:44,709
and withdraw funds

621
00:25:45,243 --> 00:25:46,478
from the supervised account

622
00:25:46,478 --> 00:25:47,045
according to the agreed plan

623
00:25:47,078 --> 00:25:48,280
to cover your daughter's future

624
00:25:48,313 --> 00:25:49,514
necessary living expenses,

625
00:25:50,148 --> 00:25:52,183
as well as medical and education costs.

626
00:25:52,784 --> 00:25:53,919
In the future, if

627
00:25:54,152 --> 00:25:55,554
you become unable to make

628
00:25:55,687 --> 00:25:56,922
your own medical decisions,

629
00:25:57,289 --> 00:25:58,189
all related

630
00:25:58,323 --> 00:25:59,391
major matters

631
00:25:59,557 --> 00:26:00,558
can also be decided

632
00:26:00,592 --> 00:26:01,526
jointly by the three of them.

633
00:26:03,795 --> 00:26:05,931
All right. Thank you, Attorney Zhu.

634
00:26:06,331 --> 00:26:06,798
It's no trouble.

635
00:26:07,265 --> 00:26:08,266
The notary staff will arrive this afternoon.

636
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,134
The appointment is at three.

637
00:26:09,534 --> 00:26:10,235
I'll take my leave now.

638
00:26:10,769 --> 00:26:11,870
Okay. Thank you. Sorry for the trouble.

639
00:26:11,870 --> 00:26:12,637
Thank you. Goodbye.

640
00:26:12,637 --> 00:26:13,038
See you this afternoon.

641
00:26:16,241 --> 00:26:16,875
This is wonderful.

642
00:26:18,076 --> 00:26:19,344
For more than ten years,

643
00:26:19,744 --> 00:26:21,913
every time things were hardest,

644
00:26:22,113 --> 00:26:22,914
you were all there

645
00:26:23,248 --> 00:26:24,950
for Linlang and me.

646
00:26:25,750 --> 00:26:26,851
What are you saying?

647
00:26:27,152 --> 00:26:28,586
Say something that formal again

648
00:26:28,787 --> 00:26:29,254
and you'll get slapped.

649
00:26:29,955 --> 00:26:31,556
Exactly. Slapped.

650
00:26:32,524 --> 00:26:33,224
Why be so polite?

651
00:26:33,325 --> 00:26:33,959
Slow down. Slow down.

652
00:26:35,727 --> 00:26:36,928
Auntie, Second Auntie, Third Auntie.

653
00:26:37,128 --> 00:26:38,430
Mom has another examination soon.

654
00:26:38,630 --> 00:26:39,864
I'll go with her.

655
00:26:40,332 --> 00:26:41,333
We'll come too.

656
00:26:41,600 --> 00:26:42,968
No need. You rest first.

657
00:26:43,068 --> 00:26:45,103
Only one family member is allowed each time.

658
00:26:45,437 --> 00:26:46,871
She's used to it anyway.

659
00:26:48,506 --> 00:26:50,375
It's also a chance for me to talk with Linlang.

660
00:26:51,209 --> 00:26:51,610
All right.

661
00:26:51,710 --> 00:26:52,110
Okay.

662
00:26:56,114 --> 00:26:57,349
There have been so many comments

663
00:26:57,349 --> 00:26:58,316
under your Weibo lately,

664
00:26:58,516 --> 00:26:59,951
all praising your new book.

665
00:27:00,719 --> 00:27:01,353
Yes.

666
00:27:02,320 --> 00:27:03,922
The second set was only just published,

667
00:27:04,656 --> 00:27:06,558
and readers are already asking for the third.

668
00:27:07,158 --> 00:27:07,993
How wonderful.

669
00:27:08,326 --> 00:27:09,894
So many people like you

670
00:27:09,928 --> 00:27:10,562
and love you.

671
00:27:11,129 --> 00:27:12,364
Mom, you are

672
00:27:12,564 --> 00:27:13,765
the cutest treasure in the whole world.

673
00:27:15,233 --> 00:27:15,767
Big Sister.

674
00:27:16,601 --> 00:27:18,103
These were shipped from Yunnan—

675
00:27:18,103 --> 00:27:19,104
blueberries.

676
00:27:19,304 --> 00:27:19,871
Take them and eat.

677
00:27:20,639 --> 00:27:21,806
You've all done so much

678
00:27:21,873 --> 00:27:23,241
to care for Xiaoli and her daughter.

679
00:27:23,441 --> 00:27:24,209
It's only right.

680
00:27:24,409 --> 00:27:25,810
Being hospitalized is hard for everyone.

681
00:27:26,111 --> 00:27:27,145
We help each other.

682
00:27:27,445 --> 00:27:28,079
Exactly.

683
00:27:28,246 --> 00:27:29,114
You've worked hard too.

684
00:27:29,681 --> 00:27:30,115
It's fine.

685
00:27:30,615 --> 00:27:31,850
Why is it you people again?

686
00:27:34,252 --> 00:27:34,886
Ma'am.

687
00:27:35,286 --> 00:27:37,255
Where are Xiaoli and Linlang?

688
00:27:38,723 --> 00:27:39,824
Why are you looking for them?

689
00:27:41,126 --> 00:27:42,927
That's a ridiculous question.

690
00:27:43,328 --> 00:27:44,229
One is my daughter,

691
00:27:44,329 --> 00:27:45,363
and the other is my granddaughter.

692
00:27:45,830 --> 00:27:48,199
Do I need your permission to see them?

693
00:27:49,401 --> 00:27:50,135
All right, enough.

694
00:27:50,335 --> 00:27:51,803
How unreasonable.

695
00:27:53,304 --> 00:27:54,439
People often say

696
00:27:55,273 --> 00:27:56,875
you only understand your parents' love

697
00:27:58,109 --> 00:27:59,711
after becoming a parent.

698
00:27:59,744 --> 00:28:00,478
But after having you,

699
00:28:01,246 --> 00:28:02,847
I finally understood

700
00:28:02,914 --> 00:28:04,149
what it truly means

701
00:28:05,517 --> 00:28:06,751
for parents to love their child.

702
00:28:07,185 --> 00:28:08,386
And I finally admitted

703
00:28:09,087 --> 00:28:09,788
that my own parents

704
00:28:11,456 --> 00:28:12,824
didn't love me.

705
00:28:13,525 --> 00:28:14,959
Because becoming your mother

706
00:28:15,560 --> 00:28:17,295
let me truly experience

707
00:28:17,429 --> 00:28:19,164
what it feels like

708
00:28:19,230 --> 00:28:20,231
to love someone unconditionally

709
00:28:20,532 --> 00:28:21,733
and to be loved unconditionally.

710
00:28:22,534 --> 00:28:23,835
Raising you

711
00:28:24,502 --> 00:28:26,104
was like raising myself

712
00:28:28,506 --> 00:28:29,274
So,

713
00:28:30,608 --> 00:28:32,277
no matter how the surgery turns out,

714
00:28:32,677 --> 00:28:34,479
Mom will never regret it.

715
00:28:37,015 --> 00:28:37,582
Linlang.

716
00:28:39,250 --> 00:28:41,920
Has Mom ever thanked you?

717
00:28:44,989 --> 00:28:45,623
For what?

718
00:28:47,192 --> 00:28:49,494
For coming into my life as my daughter.

719
00:28:54,632 --> 00:28:56,201
I'll take good care of myself.

720
00:28:57,502 --> 00:28:58,069
Mom,

721
00:28:59,270 --> 00:29:01,005
you have to get through this too.

722
00:29:01,873 --> 00:29:03,208
Let's keep fighting together, okay?

723
00:29:05,009 --> 00:29:05,510
Okay.

724
00:29:06,077 --> 00:29:07,245
We'll keep fighting together.

725
00:29:07,846 --> 00:29:08,146
Here.

726
00:29:11,049 --> 00:29:12,083
The lawyer contacted me.

727
00:29:12,317 --> 00:29:13,985
She said Xiaoli left

728
00:29:14,319 --> 00:29:15,887
a legally required share of the estate for me and her father.

729
00:29:17,055 --> 00:29:17,756
What does that mean?

730
00:29:18,123 --> 00:29:19,791
As if we need her scraps.

731
00:29:20,225 --> 00:29:21,593
It's my daughter's hard-earned money.

732
00:29:22,327 --> 00:29:23,728
I won't let outsiders get their hands on it.

733
00:29:24,262 --> 00:29:24,896
Ma'am,

734
00:29:25,163 --> 00:29:26,931
we're not after Xiaoli's money.

735
00:29:27,165 --> 00:29:28,266
The money is for Linlang.

736
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:29,968
We're only joint supervisors.

737
00:29:31,970 --> 00:29:32,637
She's foolish,

738
00:29:32,770 --> 00:29:33,671
but I'm not.

739
00:29:34,005 --> 00:29:35,406
Her whole family isn't dead yet.

740
00:29:35,774 --> 00:29:36,074
You...

741
00:29:36,107 --> 00:29:37,008
I won't agree.

742
00:29:37,242 --> 00:29:38,443
Whether you agree doesn't matter.

743
00:29:38,610 --> 00:29:40,512
The legal documents are already signed.

744
00:29:41,212 --> 00:29:42,447
You're lucky she left you anything.

745
00:29:42,480 --> 00:29:42,914
Let me tell you,

746
00:29:42,914 --> 00:29:43,648
if it were up to me,

747
00:29:43,681 --> 00:29:45,083
I wouldn't leave you a cent.

748
00:29:45,583 --> 00:29:46,451
Let me tell you,

749
00:29:47,252 --> 00:29:48,653
we are her biological parents.

750
00:29:48,853 --> 00:29:50,488
I raised her for twenty-three years.

751
00:29:50,755 --> 00:29:51,956
Did we raise an ungrateful child?

752
00:29:52,123 --> 00:29:53,224
You have the nerve to call yourselves...

753
00:29:54,626 --> 00:29:55,560
You have the nerve to say you're

754
00:29:55,693 --> 00:29:56,494
her biological parents?

755
00:29:57,095 --> 00:29:58,229
People even take cats and dogs

756
00:29:58,229 --> 00:29:58,596
to the vet

757
00:29:58,663 --> 00:29:59,931
when they get sick.

758
00:30:00,064 --> 00:30:01,533
Xiaoli has had heart disease since childhood.

759
00:30:01,566 --> 00:30:02,200
Did you ever care?

760
00:30:02,600 --> 00:30:04,235
We didn't understand.

761
00:30:04,469 --> 00:30:05,770
You keep digging up old grievances.

762
00:30:05,904 --> 00:30:06,871
What's the point?

763
00:30:07,105 --> 00:30:08,673
Xiaoli divorced right after giving birth.

764
00:30:08,907 --> 00:30:09,908
She was ill herself

765
00:30:10,008 --> 00:30:10,975
and had a nursing baby.

766
00:30:11,910 --> 00:30:12,443
Do you know how hard that was?

767
00:30:12,644 --> 00:30:13,912
You're a mother. Don't you understand?

768
00:30:14,012 --> 00:30:14,646
And another thing:

769
00:30:15,113 --> 00:30:16,481
when Linlang was just over a year old,

770
00:30:16,548 --> 00:30:17,015
she had a fever

771
00:30:17,115 --> 00:30:18,116
and even convulsed.

772
00:30:18,550 --> 00:30:19,651
Xiaoli had no one else,

773
00:30:20,051 --> 00:30:21,786
so she called me crying.

774
00:30:22,086 --> 00:30:22,921
Both mother and daughter

775
00:30:22,921 --> 00:30:23,922
had fevers over forty degrees.

776
00:30:23,988 --> 00:30:24,956
The ambulance came

777
00:30:25,089 --> 00:30:26,891
and took them both away.

778
00:30:27,192 --> 00:30:28,393
Where were their own parents then?

779
00:30:28,693 --> 00:30:29,694
Do you know how

780
00:30:29,727 --> 00:30:30,628
they survived all these years?

781
00:30:31,362 --> 00:30:32,330
Who told her to be so stubborn?

782
00:30:32,664 --> 00:30:33,798
She had a perfectly good life

783
00:30:33,932 --> 00:30:34,666
and insisted on divorcing.

784
00:30:35,633 --> 00:30:37,569
She humiliated her parents.

785
00:30:38,203 --> 00:30:38,970
Wasn't it you

786
00:30:38,970 --> 00:30:40,004
who found her such a wonderful husband?

787
00:30:40,505 --> 00:30:41,206
Two daughters:

788
00:30:41,272 --> 00:30:42,173
one married someone powerful,

789
00:30:42,207 --> 00:30:43,441
the other someone rich.

790
00:30:43,908 --> 00:30:45,176
Parents like you

791
00:30:45,476 --> 00:30:46,611
treat children as tools,

792
00:30:48,079 --> 00:30:48,880
as assets.

793
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:51,015
The only thing you never treated her as

794
00:30:51,249 --> 00:30:52,717
was a person.

795
00:30:52,951 --> 00:30:54,652
He hit her before she was even out of confinement,

796
00:30:54,919 --> 00:30:56,120
and you still wouldn't let Xiaoli divorce.

797
00:30:56,120 --> 00:30:57,088
Let me tell you, as long as we're here,

798
00:30:57,121 --> 00:30:57,522
you will never control her again.

799
00:30:57,655 --> 00:30:58,122
Exactly.

800
00:31:02,160 --> 00:31:03,161
Exactly.

801
00:31:04,095 --> 00:31:06,798
What are you doing?

802
00:31:06,798 --> 00:31:07,832
Oh my God.

803
00:31:08,166 --> 00:31:09,601
Just let her sit.

804
00:31:09,834 --> 00:31:11,603
Oh my God.

805
00:31:11,669 --> 00:31:12,604
We struggled so hard to raise her.

806
00:31:12,904 --> 00:31:13,371
Ma'am. Ma'am.

807
00:31:13,404 --> 00:31:14,038
Ma'am.

808
00:31:14,172 --> 00:31:15,206
Please listen to me.

809
00:31:15,273 --> 00:31:16,774
You can't make a scene here.

810
00:31:16,808 --> 00:31:17,208
You'll disturb the other patients.

811
00:31:17,508 --> 00:31:18,743
All right?

812
00:31:19,010 --> 00:31:19,911
Don't touch me.

813
00:31:19,944 --> 00:31:20,879
I'm warning you,

814
00:31:21,212 --> 00:31:21,913
I'm sick all over.

815
00:31:22,013 --> 00:31:23,214
If you touch me,

816
00:31:23,514 --> 00:31:24,849
I'll collapse on you.

817
00:31:25,316 --> 00:31:26,184
No one's touching you, ma'am.

818
00:31:26,284 --> 00:31:26,684
Please don't get agitated.

819
00:31:26,751 --> 00:31:27,485
Look, this

820
00:31:27,518 --> 00:31:28,052
won't solve anything,

821
00:31:28,253 --> 00:31:28,987
will it?

822
00:31:29,053 --> 00:31:30,121
Whatever's wrong,

823
00:31:30,288 --> 00:31:30,788
talk to us calmly.

824
00:31:31,089 --> 00:31:32,290
All right?

825
00:31:32,590 --> 00:31:33,791
There's no way to talk calmly.

826
00:31:33,892 --> 00:31:34,158
You two are doctors, right?

827
00:31:34,826 --> 00:31:35,627
Yes.

828
00:31:35,760 --> 00:31:36,928
Let me tell you,

829
00:31:37,295 --> 00:31:38,196
I'm You Xiaoli's mother.

830
00:31:38,363 --> 00:31:39,430
Her surgery

831
00:31:39,564 --> 00:31:40,398
cannot happen without my signature

832
00:31:40,765 --> 00:31:41,666
or my consent.

833
00:31:42,200 --> 00:31:43,368
If any of you performs it,

834
00:31:43,735 --> 00:31:44,669
I won't let you get away with it.

835
00:31:44,802 --> 00:31:45,470
Grandma.

836
00:31:46,838 --> 00:31:47,305
Mom.

837
00:31:47,872 --> 00:31:48,406
Xiaoli.

838
00:31:48,840 --> 00:31:49,707
Don't get angry.

839
00:31:49,908 --> 00:31:50,608
Don't be upset.

840
00:31:52,477 --> 00:31:52,944
I'm fine.

841
00:31:54,312 --> 00:31:55,213
Don't worry.

842
00:31:57,482 --> 00:31:58,283
Hello, Ms. You.

843
00:31:59,350 --> 00:32:00,985
Hello, Attorney Zhu.

844
00:32:03,087 --> 00:32:04,188
You've seen her clearly.

845
00:32:05,523 --> 00:32:07,091
This is my mother.

846
00:32:08,226 --> 00:32:10,094
As we previously agreed,

847
00:32:11,062 --> 00:32:12,563
regarding the share reserved for my parents,

848
00:32:12,797 --> 00:32:14,265
if they have no objections,

849
00:32:15,333 --> 00:32:16,634
the agreement will be carried out.

850
00:32:18,303 --> 00:32:19,570
If they make trouble,

851
00:32:21,306 --> 00:32:23,074
whether by causing a scene or filing a lawsuit,

852
00:32:25,009 --> 00:32:26,644
their share will be revoked.

853
00:32:28,246 --> 00:32:29,948
They have their own source of income.

854
00:32:32,450 --> 00:32:32,951
And

855
00:32:34,285 --> 00:32:35,753
to protect the physical and mental health

856
00:32:35,787 --> 00:32:36,854
of the minor,

857
00:32:38,790 --> 00:32:40,591
they will be prohibited from visiting my daughter.

858
00:32:41,993 --> 00:32:42,427
All right.

859
00:32:42,694 --> 00:32:43,328
I understand.

860
00:32:44,128 --> 00:32:45,229
I'll draft

861
00:32:45,263 --> 00:32:45,997
an additional clause.

862
00:32:46,230 --> 00:32:47,765
Please also remind your friends

863
00:32:47,932 --> 00:32:48,533
to collect

864
00:32:48,566 --> 00:32:49,600
and preserve any relevant evidence.

865
00:32:55,606 --> 00:32:56,040
Okay.

866
00:32:57,675 --> 00:32:58,242
Thank you.

867
00:33:14,192 --> 00:33:15,426
You're a mother too.

868
00:33:17,195 --> 00:33:18,396
You have a daughter.

869
00:33:20,031 --> 00:33:21,132
If you treat me this way,

870
00:33:21,766 --> 00:33:22,967
your daughter is watching.

871
00:33:24,235 --> 00:33:24,869
Later,

872
00:33:25,269 --> 00:33:26,237
she'll copy your example.

873
00:33:28,439 --> 00:33:30,108
How my daughter treats me

874
00:33:31,175 --> 00:33:32,844
depends on how I treat her.

875
00:33:35,013 --> 00:33:36,214
Each generation is responsible for the next.

876
00:33:37,682 --> 00:33:38,683
My sister's life and mine

877
00:33:38,716 --> 00:33:40,084
have already been controlled by you.

878
00:33:43,521 --> 00:33:44,489
My daughter

879
00:33:45,690 --> 00:33:47,525
will never be manipulated by you.

880
00:33:50,228 --> 00:33:50,728
Mom.

881
00:33:51,129 --> 00:33:52,196
Don't come again.

882
00:34:00,972 --> 00:34:01,572
What are you looking at?

883
00:34:02,607 --> 00:34:03,408
There's nothing to see.

884
00:34:04,842 --> 00:34:05,643
Everyone, disperse.

885
00:34:06,411 --> 00:34:06,811
Go back.

886
00:34:06,844 --> 00:34:07,812
Mom, are you okay?

887
00:34:07,812 --> 00:34:08,913
Thank you, Dr. Qiao.

888
00:34:09,447 --> 00:34:10,014
I'm fine.

889
00:34:24,829 --> 00:34:25,463
You Xiaoli,

890
00:34:26,264 --> 00:34:27,465
we're starting anesthesia now.

891
00:34:28,232 --> 00:34:28,866
Don't worry.

892
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:29,967
You'll be fine when you wake up.

893
00:34:32,303 --> 00:34:32,970
We're beginning.

894
00:34:46,751 --> 00:34:49,520
I really miss university life.

895
00:34:50,855 --> 00:34:52,290
Those were

896
00:34:52,490 --> 00:34:53,791
the happiest four years of my life.

897
00:34:55,293 --> 00:34:57,095
I never imagined that in the blink of an eye,

898
00:34:57,495 --> 00:34:59,063
we'd all become mothers.

899
00:35:00,398 --> 00:35:02,233
And you're still the youngest mom.

900
00:35:03,367 --> 00:35:04,402
How wonderful.

901
00:35:04,635 --> 00:35:06,003
We've been out of school for twenty years

902
00:35:06,304 --> 00:35:07,171
and we're still together.

903
00:35:07,572 --> 00:35:08,639
What are you saying?

904
00:35:09,273 --> 00:35:10,041
Even in another twenty years,

905
00:35:10,074 --> 00:35:11,042
we still won't drift apart.

906
00:35:11,843 --> 00:35:12,410
When we...

907
00:35:13,110 --> 00:35:13,711
Keep your voice down.

908
00:35:13,711 --> 00:35:14,912
When we're old ladies,

909
00:35:15,213 --> 00:35:16,447
we'll travel around the world.

910
00:35:17,115 --> 00:35:17,748
On a cruise.

911
00:35:17,815 --> 00:35:18,816
Didn't you always want to take a cruise?

912
00:35:19,317 --> 00:35:19,951
That's right.

913
00:35:20,084 --> 00:35:21,352
A cruise around the world.

914
00:35:22,487 --> 00:35:23,354
Will you even be able to walk then?

915
00:35:23,788 --> 00:35:24,388
Of course I will.

916
00:35:29,994 --> 00:35:31,796
Linlang is very sensible.

917
00:35:33,564 --> 00:35:35,266
She's also quite independent.

918
00:35:36,667 --> 00:35:38,803
She's just a little young now.

919
00:35:39,770 --> 00:35:40,805
In another two or three years,

920
00:35:41,572 --> 00:35:43,040
things will be better.

921
00:35:43,908 --> 00:35:44,809
She'll be able

922
00:35:44,842 --> 00:35:45,643
to take even better care of herself.

923
00:35:46,344 --> 00:35:47,612
Why are you in such a hurry?

924
00:35:48,112 --> 00:35:49,881
Linlang will grow up little by little.

925
00:35:50,248 --> 00:35:52,083
We'll all still be here then.

926
00:35:52,183 --> 00:35:52,650
Exactly.

927
00:35:54,752 --> 00:35:55,553
And besides,

928
00:35:56,053 --> 00:35:57,555
Linlang will always be our child.

929
00:35:57,655 --> 00:35:58,389
Right.

930
00:35:59,223 --> 00:36:01,192
Don't think about anything else.

931
00:36:01,526 --> 00:36:02,627
Put your mind at ease

932
00:36:02,693 --> 00:36:03,594
and focus on the surgery.

933
00:36:03,928 --> 00:36:05,229
Right. While you're in surgery,

934
00:36:05,363 --> 00:36:06,597
we'll look after her for you.

935
00:36:07,064 --> 00:36:07,932
Don't worry.

936
00:36:08,065 --> 00:36:09,133
If anyone dares bully her,

937
00:36:09,166 --> 00:36:10,601
the three of us will stand up for her.

938
00:36:11,168 --> 00:36:12,103
You alone would be enough.

939
00:36:15,373 --> 00:36:15,973
True.

940
00:36:16,641 --> 00:36:18,009
All three of you should go together.

941
00:36:18,209 --> 00:36:19,544
I'm not worried about Linlang.

942
00:36:20,244 --> 00:36:21,612
I'm worried about the person facing you.

943
00:36:22,413 --> 00:36:23,548
Of course.

944
00:37:34,552 --> 00:37:35,086
By the way,

945
00:37:35,953 --> 00:37:37,521
back at school,

946
00:37:37,521 --> 00:37:39,190
we were known as the four great beauties.

947
00:37:40,191 --> 00:37:42,193
One, two, three... the four beauties.

948
00:37:42,293 --> 00:37:43,494
Let's take a group photo.

949
00:37:43,728 --> 00:37:44,595
Sure.

950
00:37:44,729 --> 00:37:45,630
The Four Golden Flowers.

951
00:37:45,796 --> 00:37:46,364
Come on, take it.

952
00:37:46,530 --> 00:37:47,331
The phone's here.

953
00:37:47,865 --> 00:37:48,666
Third Sister takes good photos.

954
00:37:48,799 --> 00:37:49,634
Exactly. Come on.

955
00:37:50,234 --> 00:37:50,668
Slowly.

956
00:37:50,668 --> 00:37:51,669
Turn on the beauty filter.

957
00:37:52,336 --> 00:37:53,004
Come on, get ready.

958
00:37:53,004 --> 00:37:53,504
Look here.

959
00:37:53,671 --> 00:37:56,040
One, two, three.

960
00:37:56,040 --> 00:37:56,474
You can do it.

961
00:38:00,878 --> 00:38:01,712
The patient is You Xiaoli,

962
00:38:02,013 --> 00:38:02,680
45 years old.

963
00:38:03,347 --> 00:38:04,248
She underwent VSD repair

964
00:38:04,749 --> 00:38:05,983
and aortic valve replacement.

965
00:38:06,183 --> 00:38:06,784
The surgery went smoothly.

966
00:38:07,918 --> 00:38:09,120
She also had the aortic valve replaced?

967
00:38:09,954 --> 00:38:11,055
I remember the preoperative examination

968
00:38:11,088 --> 00:38:12,123
showed moderate regurgitation.

969
00:38:13,591 --> 00:38:15,559
Intraoperative transesophageal echocardiography found

970
00:38:15,593 --> 00:38:16,761
it had progressed to moderate-to-severe.

971
00:38:18,029 --> 00:38:18,496
Head Nurse,

972
00:38:19,630 --> 00:38:20,264
give her more

973
00:38:20,598 --> 00:38:21,265
inhaled nitric oxide.

974
00:38:21,766 --> 00:38:22,600
Don't extubate too early.

975
00:38:23,434 --> 00:38:25,336
Maintain deep sedation

976
00:38:25,503 --> 00:38:26,404
for the first 24 hours.

977
00:38:26,437 --> 00:38:27,204
After 24 hours,

978
00:38:27,371 --> 00:38:27,838
let her wake up gradually.

979
00:38:36,881 --> 00:38:38,249
Understood.

980
00:38:38,349 --> 00:38:39,450
I've arranged the shifts and posted them in the group.

981
00:38:39,784 --> 00:38:41,452
Everyone check them later.

982
00:38:41,485 --> 00:38:42,753
For the next two days, make sure

983
00:38:42,987 --> 00:38:44,522
someone is at You Xiaoli's bedside at all times.

984
00:38:44,522 --> 00:38:45,322
Upload the data and photos every hour

985
00:38:45,456 --> 00:38:46,590
to the group.

986
00:38:46,891 --> 00:38:48,192
I can see them there too.

987
00:38:48,426 --> 00:38:49,393
Share everything immediately

988
00:38:49,694 --> 00:38:50,094
and summarize and compare the changes.

989
00:38:50,327 --> 00:38:50,895
Understood.

990
00:38:51,095 --> 00:38:52,063
Don't worry, Professor.

991
00:38:52,163 --> 00:38:52,830
I'll stay here tonight

992
00:38:53,164 --> 00:38:54,198
and won't go anywhere.

993
00:38:54,432 --> 00:38:55,533
I'm on duty in the ICU.

994
00:38:55,633 --> 00:38:56,534
Call me if anything happens.

995
00:38:56,767 --> 00:38:57,134
I'll come immediately.

996
00:39:24,829 --> 00:39:25,629
All right.

997
00:39:27,131 --> 00:39:28,065
You caught a cold, didn't you?

998
00:39:29,533 --> 00:39:30,868
Maybe I got a little chilled.

999
00:39:30,968 --> 00:39:32,336
Auntie, you really do have a cold.

1000
00:39:32,403 --> 00:39:33,270
You need to take care of yourself.

1001
00:39:35,072 --> 00:39:36,040
You haven't even been drinking water.

1002
00:39:36,273 --> 00:39:37,608
I brought you medicine, Big Sister.

1003
00:39:37,842 --> 00:39:38,976
Take it in a moment.

1004
00:39:39,510 --> 00:39:40,344
I'll stay tonight instead.

1005
00:39:40,344 --> 00:39:41,512
Go home and get a proper night's sleep.

1006
00:39:42,680 --> 00:39:43,080
Thank you.

1007
00:39:44,081 --> 00:39:45,116
Director Sheng said

1008
00:39:45,149 --> 00:39:46,650
Mom's surgery went well.

1009
00:39:46,884 --> 00:39:47,852
You've all taken leave

1010
00:39:47,852 --> 00:39:48,652
and been here for so long.

1011
00:39:48,786 --> 00:39:49,787
You can't keep doing this.

1012
00:39:50,187 --> 00:39:50,988
You should all go home.

1013
00:39:51,122 --> 00:39:51,922
I can manage by myself.

1014
00:39:52,022 --> 00:39:53,124
How could we?

1015
00:39:53,824 --> 00:39:54,225
Enough.

1016
00:39:54,525 --> 00:39:55,793
You all live far away.

1017
00:39:56,026 --> 00:39:56,894
Go home.

1018
00:39:57,595 --> 00:39:59,196
I already live in Dongjiang.

1019
00:39:59,830 --> 00:40:00,431
For the next few days,

1020
00:40:00,731 --> 00:40:01,532
Linlang and I

1021
00:40:01,565 --> 00:40:02,733
can take turns.

1022
00:40:03,134 --> 00:40:03,934
You all go home.

1023
00:40:07,705 --> 00:40:08,205
Linlang,

1024
00:40:08,606 --> 00:40:09,607
take good care of yourself.

1025
00:40:15,479 --> 00:40:15,913
Brother.

1026
00:40:16,747 --> 00:40:17,314
What's wrong?

1027
00:40:17,414 --> 00:40:18,282
You sounded so excited on the phone.

1028
00:40:18,449 --> 00:40:19,483
I just ran into Director Ji

1029
00:40:19,517 --> 00:40:20,351
and suddenly had an idea.

1030
00:40:20,885 --> 00:40:22,286
We haven't been able to get

1031
00:40:22,319 --> 00:40:23,387
our cardiomyopathy gene project approved, right?

1032
00:40:24,155 --> 00:40:25,089
What if we don't apply

1033
00:40:25,122 --> 00:40:26,390
through the Heart Center?

1034
00:40:28,392 --> 00:40:30,361
You mean through the ICU?

1035
00:40:30,628 --> 00:40:30,995
Exactly.

1036
00:40:31,395 --> 00:40:32,363
The ICU

1037
00:40:32,396 --> 00:40:33,531
has a complete laboratory

1038
00:40:33,564 --> 00:40:34,398
and all the other resources.

1039
00:40:34,632 --> 00:40:35,933
As long as Director Ji supports us,

1040
00:40:36,066 --> 00:40:37,368
President Wang can't easily block it.

1041
00:40:38,002 --> 00:40:38,502
Good idea.

1042
00:40:40,638 --> 00:40:41,438
That's a brilliant idea.

1043
00:40:41,772 --> 00:40:42,606
Why are you here?

1044
00:40:42,807 --> 00:40:43,474
I've been here the whole time.

1045
00:40:43,908 --> 00:40:44,842
You startled me.

1046
00:40:46,277 --> 00:40:47,144
I think it could work too.

1047
00:40:47,511 --> 00:40:48,612
Then you should lead it.

1048
00:40:49,613 --> 00:40:51,015
But I'm a little worried.

1049
00:40:51,148 --> 00:40:52,783
I'm only an attending physician.

1050
00:40:52,917 --> 00:40:53,884
What's there to worry about?

1051
00:40:53,918 --> 00:40:55,252
You're an excellent attending.

1052
00:40:55,286 --> 00:40:55,853
Dr. Fang.

1053
00:40:56,554 --> 00:40:57,521
I support it. I'm joining.

1054
00:40:59,290 --> 00:41:00,224
Do we need him?

1055
00:41:01,759 --> 00:41:02,593
Other than operating,

1056
00:41:02,593 --> 00:41:03,227
what else can you do?

1057
00:41:03,327 --> 00:41:03,694
I...

1058
00:41:04,762 --> 00:41:05,930
I can do plenty.

1059
00:41:05,930 --> 00:41:06,564
I'm telling you,

1060
00:41:06,964 --> 00:41:09,667
I just contribute quietly.

1061
00:41:10,401 --> 00:41:10,968
Right?

1062
00:41:13,404 --> 00:41:14,605
Then I'll prepare the application report.

1063
00:41:14,705 --> 00:41:15,873
I'll talk to Director Ji.

1064
00:41:16,040 --> 00:41:16,507
I'll go

1065
00:41:20,711 --> 00:41:22,079
see what I can do.

1066
00:41:28,052 --> 00:41:28,719
Make porridge.

1067
00:41:30,087 --> 00:41:30,554
Xiao Du.

1068
00:41:30,955 --> 00:41:31,555
What is it?

1069
00:41:33,524 --> 00:41:34,325
Okay. I'm coming right away.

1070
00:41:40,331 --> 00:41:40,731
Xiao Du.

1071
00:41:41,432 --> 00:41:41,832
Professor Fang.

1072
00:41:42,132 --> 00:41:42,433
Director.

1073
00:41:44,001 --> 00:41:44,668
Her condition is deteriorating.

1074
00:41:45,336 --> 00:41:46,470
At first, with ventilator support

1075
00:41:46,503 --> 00:41:47,838
and inhaled nitric oxide,

1076
00:41:48,005 --> 00:41:49,507
all her indicators were normal.

1077
00:41:49,673 --> 00:41:51,275
Her pulmonary artery pressure also fell.

1078
00:41:51,575 --> 00:41:52,610
But after extubation,

1079
00:41:52,743 --> 00:41:54,411
her oxygen saturation kept dropping.

1080
00:41:54,678 --> 00:41:55,913
Her cardiac function continued to worsen.

1081
00:41:56,947 --> 00:41:57,848
We started

1082
00:41:57,882 --> 00:41:58,716
high-flow oxygen therapy.

1083
00:41:58,816 --> 00:41:59,383
But

1084
00:41:59,483 --> 00:42:00,384
her oxygen saturation

1085
00:42:00,451 --> 00:42:01,285
still can't recover

1086
00:42:01,318 --> 00:42:02,353
to above 90 percent.

1087
00:42:02,653 --> 00:42:03,787
Her blood pressure is barely holding too.

1088
00:42:04,188 --> 00:42:05,489
The right heart failure is severe.

1089
00:42:05,589 --> 00:42:07,291
The shunt has reversed right-to-left.

1090
00:42:07,391 --> 00:42:08,792
Her chest X-ray and sputum culture indicate

1091
00:42:08,893 --> 00:42:09,894
a pulmonary infection.

1092
00:42:10,160 --> 00:42:11,161
Acinetobacter baumannii.

1093
00:42:11,328 --> 00:42:12,596
We used antibiotics,

1094
00:42:12,763 --> 00:42:13,764
but they haven't worked.

1095
00:42:14,465 --> 00:42:15,399
Acute right heart failure.

1096
00:42:16,133 --> 00:42:17,234
What we feared has happened.

1097
00:42:19,403 --> 00:42:20,170
What do we do next?

1098
00:42:20,271 --> 00:42:20,804
ECMO.

1099
00:42:21,572 --> 00:42:22,573
Wait for a heart-lung transplant.

1100
00:42:23,073 --> 00:42:23,807
But no one knows

1101
00:42:23,841 --> 00:42:25,209
when a donor will become available.

1102
00:42:25,643 --> 00:42:26,644
With heart failure this severe,

1103
00:42:26,844 --> 00:42:27,511
even on ECMO,

1104
00:42:27,545 --> 00:42:28,345
the outcome is uncertain.

1105
00:42:28,612 --> 00:42:29,680
We can only take it one step at a time.

1106
00:42:30,814 --> 00:42:31,615
Has Director Sheng come by?

1107
00:42:32,082 --> 00:42:32,950
After the post-op handoff,

1108
00:42:32,983 --> 00:42:34,084
he hasn't returned.

1109
00:42:34,485 --> 00:42:35,653
He called once

1110
00:42:35,920 --> 00:42:37,187
and only told us to monitor closely.

1111
00:42:41,792 --> 00:42:43,027
The patient's condition is critical.

1112
00:42:43,193 --> 00:42:43,827
We're worried

1113
00:42:43,827 --> 00:42:44,828
she may not last more than a few days.

1114
00:42:45,496 --> 00:42:46,430
She has signed the consent form.

1115
00:42:46,463 --> 00:42:47,398
She's also been registered for a donor.

1116
00:42:47,865 --> 00:42:48,866
Sorry to trouble you, Professor Guo.

1117
00:42:49,400 --> 00:42:50,401
I understand, Director Zhou.

1118
00:42:50,434 --> 00:42:51,468
We've been monitoring continuously.

1119
00:42:51,635 --> 00:42:52,670
We've been monitoring continuously.

1120
00:42:52,670 --> 00:42:53,504
As soon as a donor becomes available,

1121
00:42:53,504 --> 00:42:54,405
we'll notify your center immediately.

1122
00:42:54,572 --> 00:42:55,439
Okay. Thank you.
